text: Ketevan "Keto" Losaberidze (, 1 August 1949 – 23 January 2022) was a Georgian archer. She competed for the Soviet Union at the 1972 and 1980 Olympics. She won a gold medal in 1980, becoming the only Soviet Olympic champion in archery. She was born in Tqibuli, Georgian SSR, Soviet Union. Losaberidze died on 23 January 2022 in Tbilisi, Georgia, at the age of 72.Умерла олимпийская чемпионка Кетеван Лосаберидзе ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Olympians for Georgia (country) Category:Olympic gold medalists for the Soviet Union Category:Archers from Georgia (country)
